transcript.sentence: Ringling college of art and design presents.
Watermelon a cautionary tale.
The screen where the text of this video is on,
then splits into slices of watermelon.
The mom puts a tray of five slices of the watermelon.
It shows jimmy running across the floor, and then his hand shoots up as he tries to get onto the chair.
He chooses a slice of watermelon. And as he is about to take a bite of it,
he paused.
He gives a smirk and look sneak iliac his mon and continues to take bites of the watermelon.
It shows one tiny seed going down the esophagus do.
It plants into a stomach. And then a plant starts growing rapidly.
His alarm starts ringing and jimmy wakes up and starts to stretch. And there are some leaves on his pillow and on his blanket.
He walks on over to his bathroom, and he sees a little thing sticking out of his nose. So he starts to pull it out.
He falls back and realizes that there are a bunch of stems and leaves all over the bathroom.
As the plank keeps growing out of his nose, he tries to sniffle it back in, but it keeps on coming out.
Even in class, while he is sitting on his desk, the plant keeps on growing out.
His teacher passes by his desk and trips on the plant and makes jimmy go outside.
He is sent to the principal's office. And while he is there,
the plant keeps on growing out of his ears and his nostrils.
The principal pulls on the plant growing out of his nostrils, and then read stuff starts to come out and he realizes that it's the watermelon juice.
Then the juice starts coming out of his nose rapidly.
His mom wipes the juice from his nose and then pulls on his eye to make sure he's okay.
While she is doing that, his eyes turn all the way around.
and they turn into the shape of a watermelon seed.
He opens his mouth. And the inside of his mouth is all slices of the watermelon.
His mom pulls out some scissors to try to cut the sam.
Then, since the plant still keeps growing, his mom pulls out a chainsaw and jimmy starts running away.
While he is running, he trips and falls onto his stomach. And then he starts sliding because the floor is slippery.
He makes it outside of the door, and his shirt flies out, showing the shape of the watermelon.
The next scene, he is racing his friends on the track.
But then he beats them since he can roll as a watermelon.
Now he has lost his face, and his whole body and face is the watermelon.
After winning the race, jimmy spots the slide
and the playground, and he wants to go over there.
He slides down the slide. He uses the seesaw. And as he jumps, seeds start flying out.
And he goes on the swings and they start going too fast. So he starts to fling off and his arms and legs disappear,
and then he splat sohn to the ground.
The kids walk over to the watermelon that has fallen on the ground. And they all start taking bites of.
After they take bites of the water mount, it shows leaves coming out of them
and
the cycle starts all over again.

CGI 3D Animated Short Film: Watermelon A Cautionary Tale Animated Short Film by Kefei Li & Connie Qin He at Ringling College of Art + Design. Featured on CGMeetup https://www.cgmeetup.com/

Watermelon: A Cautionary Tale is about a boy who accidentally eats a watermelon seed and later the seeds start to grow in his belly.

A film by Kefei Li & Connie Qin He 
Produced at Ringling College of Art and Design https://www.ringling.edu/
Music by Antonius Nazareth, Sound Designed by Nick Ainsworth.
